UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Khalid Saboor HAYNES, Defendant-Appellant. No. 06-12192

Non-Argument Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Eleventh Circuit. June 27, 2007. Thomas H. Dale, Dale Law Firm, P.A., Orlando, FL, for Defendant-Appellant. Roberta Josephina Bodnar, U.S. Attorney’s Office, Orlando, FL, for PlaintiffAppellee. Before TJOFLAT, ANDERSON and HULL, Circuit Judges. PER CURIAM:

Tom Dale, appointed counsel for Khalid Saboor Haynes in this direct criminal appeal, has moved to withdraw from further representation of the appellant and filed a brief pursuant to Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967). Our independent review of the entire record reveals that counsel’s assessment of the relative merit of the appeal is correct. Because independent examination of the entire record reveals no arguable issues of merit, counsel’s motion to withdraw is GRANTED, and Haynes’s conviction and sentence is AFFIRMED.
